  { q: 'What does ATP mean in text?', a: 'ATP most commonly means "At This Point" in casual texting and social media. It can also mean "Answer The Phone" when someone is frustrated that you are not picking up.' },
  { q: 'How do you use ATP in a sentence?', a: '"ATP I give up" (At This Point I give up). Or: "ATP just call me" (Answer The Phone, just call me).' },
  { q: 'What does ATP mean on TikTok?', a: 'On TikTok, ATP is almost always "At This Point" — used in captions and comments to describe a situation that has gone on so long it has reached a conclusion.' },
  { q: 'Is ATP the same as ATM?', a: 'No. ATM means "At The Moment." ATP means "At This Point." ATM is about right now; ATP is about a current state or conclusion reached over time.' },
